cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE

This paper focuses on making text classifiers more interpretable, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new approach for training neural networks with binary variables, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories.
